cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories:
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper presents a technique for training low precision deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper evaluates the proposed technique on image classification datasets (MNIST and CIFAR10), which are commonly used in computer vision research.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on training neural networks and achieving model compression, which are topics related to neural computing.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper emphasizes the hardware implementation costs and benefits of the proposed technique, which is relevant to hardware architecture research.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the resource and speed benefits of the proposed technique, which are related to system and control aspects of hardware implementation.
